H.B. 1019
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Apr 21, 2026
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH40625-DFf-1
Short Title: Mike Clampitt 1st Responder Tax Fairness Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Pyrtle.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO BROADEN THE EXEMPTION FROM HIGHWAY USE TAX FOR
3 VOLUNTEER FIRE DEPARTMENTS AND RESCUE SQUADS.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 105-187.6 reads as rewritten:
6 "§ 105-187.6. Exemptions from highway use tax.
7 (a) Full Exemptions. – The tax imposed by this Article does not apply when a certificate
8 of title is issued as the result of a transfer of a motor vehicle:
9 …
10 (9) To a volunteer fire department or volunteer rescue squad that is not part of a
11 unit of local government, has no more than two paid employees, government
12 and is exempt from State income tax under G.S. 105-130.11, when the motor
13 vehicle is one of the following:G.S. 105-130.11.
14 a. A fire truck, a pump truck, a tanker truck, or a ladder truck used to
15 suppress fire.
16 b. A four-wheel drive vehicle intended to be mounted with a water tank
17 and hose and used for forest fire fighting.
18 c. An emergency services vehicle.
19 …."
20 SECTION 2. This act is effective for taxes imposed for taxable years beginning on
21 or after July 1, 2026, and applies to certificates of title issued on or after that date.
